contact_desc: Dr. Jacqueline Williams is a Licensed Marriage and Family Therapist, Qualified Supervisor, and daughter of a Veteran. With a passion for helping soldiers with the transition out of the military, using a focus on NeuroScience. She also enjoys sitting down to enjoy a good beer with anyone who wants to talk. With almost 20 years of private practice, residential, and community mental health experience she is experienced and educated in working with students and clients in the most proficient and effective ways. In her practice, she specializes in working with PTSD, Veterans, Mindfulness, couples, and helping athletes overcome mental barriers they experience before, during, and after competition. Her expansive background, research, and experience has contributed to developing successful tools to improve communication skills in her client’s relationships.
SAMHSA’s Disaster Distress Helpline provides 24/7, 365-day-a-year crisis counseling and support to people experiencing emotional distress related to natural or human-caused disasters.
A 24 hrs service that forwards your call to the nearest crisis hotline in your area determined from the your phones area code.
If you're a Veteran in crisis or concerned about one, the Veterans Crisis Line is a free, confidential resource that connects you to a real person specially trained to support Veterans.

We can all help prevent suicide. The Lifeline provides 24/7, free and confidential support for people in distress, prevention and crisis resources for you or your loved ones, and best practices for professionals in the United States.
